SABC staff in are staging a picket outside the public broadcaster’s
Auckland Park offices. The picket is an effort to save their jobs with the looming
retrenchments at the broadcaster. They plan to protest daily from next week. The public broadcaster is preparing to retrench over 981 workers. SABC chairperson Bongumusa Makhathini, said 1200 freelancers will
also be affected. The broadcaster is allegedly looking at taking productions of
several shows in-house’ The SABC issued a notice to all staff informing them of the SABC’s
intention to proceed with Section 189 of the Labour Relations Act (“LRA”). This act will affect Group Services, Provincial Operations,
Commercial Enterprises, Media Technology and Infrastructure, News, Radio, Sport
and Television. 